entry.title: Reland "[Exo]Animation fix w.r.t RecreateLayers"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 9c093584851f4fe43f845cbb43663b0fae7a82ac



Original change's description:

> [Exo]Animation fix w.r.t RecreateLayers

>

> When an animation causes the `host_window` to `RecreateLayers`, the

> animation treats the new `host_window->layer` as if it's ready to be

> shown. Before the client has time to ack to the config event for that

> request, the `old_layer` prior to the cloning should be hosting the

> incoming wl_surface commits, i.e. it's the `commit_target_layer`.

>

> If incoming commits cause the surface hierarchy to change bounds, it

> should be changing bounds of the `commit_target_layer`, instead of the

> `host_window->layer`.

>

> This CL ensures that the bounds changes from the client goes to its

> `commit_target_layer`, and updates the `viz::SurfaceId` range for the

> `host_window->layer` s.t. fallback looks correct via stretching.

>

> Changes:

> 1) `Config`: stores an extra field `old_layer` to track the Layer

> prior to cloning.

> 2) `AllocateLocalSurfaceId`: `host_window`'s parent seq_number

> increments will be suppressed if they're originated from the client

> modifying the wayland surface hierarchy.

> 3) `GetCommitTargetLayer()`: returns the ui::Layer that can host

> client's surface commits. Due to animation cancelling destroying the

> old_layer with it, this may return nullptr.

> 4) `MaybeActivateSurface()`: for ShellSurface that has a config queue,

> it updates the surface range of `old_layer`s, and `host_window`'s

> layer, to be:

> [current_surface_id, max(layer_surface_id, current_surface_id)].

> And rely on stretching fallback surface when the deadline expires.

>

> Bug: 1251778, 1468344

entry.title: [ios] Fix TabInsertionBrowserAgentTest
entry.content:
The test TabInsertionBrowserAgentTest depends on SessionServiceIOS

singleton when UseSessionSerializationOptimizations() is false. If

any tests before create the singleton, it will have a dangling

task runner and the tests will crashes.



By removing the calls to SessionRestorationService::SetSessionID()

and the SessionServiceIOS with the dangling task runner is not used.



The proper fix is to stop using the SessionServiceIOS singleton and

to have an owned instance, but this is not possible until the last

usages of the singleton in BrowsingDataRemover and SceneController

are removed.

entry.title: Fix no gl context issue in D3DImageBacking::Create*()
entry.content:
With Graphite, D3DImageBacking can be created and destroyed

without any GL context current. It will cause no gl context issue,

because we create GL texture during creating and cache textures

in the backing. Fix the problem by deferring gl texture creation

and just cache weak pointers to the gl textures. So the GL textures

will be destroyed if they are not used by any GL representations.

entry.title: Implement supports() for @import
entry.content:
As per:

https://drafts.csswg.org/css-cascade-5/#typedef-import-conditions

@import should support supports() conditions.



Currently, the CSS Supports Parser utilizes the stream parser,

while the ConsumeImportRule is based upon the token-based parser,

as the functions that parse layer(...) are token-based.



Therefore, to use the Supports Parser, the remaining token range left

after parsing the layer() is converted into a stream

and passed to the Supports Parser.

entry.title: Remove IncognitoUtils from PaymentHandlerCoordinator.
entry.content:
Instead of relying on the WindowAndroid to get the Profile, this

has access to the triggering WebContents. The Profile state is

always matching the triggering and created WebContents, so there

is no need to pass around the lossy IsOffTheRecord when this can

access the Profile directly.



The isOffTheRecord for the Payment request is calculated here:

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/android/java/src/org/chromium/chrome/browser/payments/ChromePaymentRequestFactory.java;drc=81090fd5b036f4ca06a8b04da91242f929a27068;l=75



It is using the triggered RenderFrameHost to get the Profile,

which ensures the incognito-ness of the request always matches

the page it was triggered from (e.g. you do not have an Incognito

tab trying to trigger a non-incognito Payment request). Thus, use

the existing Profile reference.
